# The Quake Shack

## Todos

Grouped by sections and then sorted by priority (more or less).

### Modern JavaScript

- [X] `COM` we need to completely get rid of synchroneously loading files, it’s flagged as deprecated
- [_] since IO is no longer blocking, things need to be more aware of stuff still stuck on loading
- [_] considering replacing Sys.Print and Con.Print with console.info, console.warn, etc.
- [_] use more Exceptions and better Exception classes, also more console.asserts
- [_] use more generator functions when possible

### UI/UX improvements

- [_] M: better multiplayer menus
  - [_] setup a profile when new player
  - [_] better create game menu
  - [_] integrate with server browser
- [X] M: make it more readible on high DPI screens
- [_] UI: textboxes should act more like text boxes
- [_] CL: finished demos trigger a `Host.Error` (lost connection), needs fixing
- [_] M: introduce a password required dialog to join password protected servers
- [_] M: touch support (how to escape etc) and mouse support
- [_] M: rewrite the code using the new framework
- [_] IN: proper virtual joystick and keyboard/UI
- [_] M: expose GUI toolkit (draw routines etc.) to the client game code, put stuff in shared/
- [_] CL: remove that chatlog stuff again, it’s all done in the Client code now

### Code smell

- [_] make clear that a function is a generator: `getFaces()` --> `facesIter()`
- [_] CL: go over the client API again, too much confusing lingo here and there after me hacking in lots of features
- [_] SV: cleanup the `SV.WriteEntitiesToClient` mess a bit, make it more flexible
- [_] cleanup `charCodeAt` everywhere
- [_] completely get rid of `Host.client`
- [_] refactor `MSG`/`SZ` especially in regards to `NET.message` and `client[…].message`
- [_] `CL.state.intermission`/`ExitIntermission`: unsure what happens next on DS
- [_] remove C style code that is almost verbatim from Quake
- [X] Mod.ForName and bmodel/submodels smells a bit funny, should be a bit more streamlined with the Async stuff
- [_] reorganize shaders

### Network improvements

- [X] port QuakeWorld netcode
- [_] flush messages more often, increase update rate
- [_] look into that weird sluggish feel when ping is >100 ms (especially on Firefox)

### Life improvements

- [_] unregister Cvars and Commands registered by the game code

### Rendering improvements

- [X] lerp view model animations
- [_] water transparency should be configured through other means such as worldspawnInfo (wateralpha, lavaalpha, telealpha, slimealpha)
- [X] texture cache can return wrong textures when they share the same name across maps but are actually different
- [_] more interesting warp: https://www.shadertoy.com/view/ctXyW8
- [_] fix lightmap datastructure, right now it’s eating up ~200 MiB
- [X] double check the fullbright texture rendering of alias ~and sprite~ models
- [_] proper func_fog functionality so that game code can change fog parameters
- [_] lod considering fog

### Random issues

- [X] a not precached resource will cause dropping Promises, game code needs model right away, QuakeC VM broken
- [_] invoking all these special Host console commands intended to be forwarded from the client or handled on a per client basis are causing issues when invoked outside of that (e.g. exec’ing color, name etc. on a dedicated server)
- [X] group animated models are not rendered anymore

### LibreQuake support

- [_] investigate issues with missing/broken bmodels in some of the maps
- [X] add back `.lit` support (right now it’s only looking for RGBLIGHTING bspxlump)
- [X] add fog support (basically read out the worldspawnInfo and configure the distance correctly)
- [_] try to get QuakeC’s progs.dat going

### Game experience breaking/degrading issues

- [X] Platforms/doors are sometimes losing the player which gets unstuck into the void
- [X] Telefragging the boss monster is not working

